messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

- TRACE: false

Explanation:
- The controller class has no class-level @RequestMapping, so no prefix applies. The method getNearestPrintShops is annotated with @RequestMapping(value = "/printshops/nearest", method = RequestMethod.GET), therefore the full path is "/printshops/nearest".
- The method explicitly declares RequestMethod.GET, so only GET is accepted according to the code.
- Per the instructions, acceptance is determined from the code annotations only. Although some frameworks may implicitly handle HEAD for GET endpoints at runtime, there is no explicit HEAD mapping in the source, so HEAD is reported as not acceptable. All other methods are likewise not declared and thus not acceptable.
